-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Origin and clean-room statement
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is an ORIGINAL, CLEAN-ROOM implementation of the publicly published
Infineon/Cypress HyperBus Specification, document 001-99253 Rev *H (Feb 6, 2019).
The RTL, testbenches, and documentation in this repository were written from that
specification. An implementation-oriented digest of the spec used during
development is included as docs/SPEC_DIGEST.md.

"HyperBus", "HyperRAM", and "HyperFlash" are trademarks of Infineon Technologies
(formerly Cypress Semiconductor). This project is an independent, unaffiliated
implementation of the openly published bus specification and is not endorsed by or
associated with Infineon Technologies. These names are used only to describe the
interface this IP implements.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Design references (consulted, NOT copied)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

During development the following open-source HyperRAM controllers were read as
references for the CORRECTNESS OF APPROACH only. No source code from either project
was copied, translated, or adapted into this repository; all HDL here is original.

  * MJoergen/HyperRAM
      Language: VHDL
      License:  MIT
      Use here: design reference only (init/latency handling, general structure).

  * OpenHBMC
      Language: Verilog
      License:  Apache License 2.0
      Use here: design reference only (latency-code / burst-chop conventions).

Device register addresses and reset values (ID0/ID1/CR0/CR1) used by the package
and the behavioral model correspond to the Winbond W957D8NB / HyperRAM device
family and were cross-checked against a device bus-functional model; the generic
HyperBus specification defers these values to each device datasheet. They are
flagged "[device, not generic spec]" throughout docs/SPEC_DIGEST.md.

